---
description: Use visual-explainer for agent-driven HTML diagrams and advisory recap pages alongside CMMC Advisor
globs: "**/*"
alwaysApply: false
---

When the user asks for a visual gap analysis, mock-assessment recap, scope-discovery
summary, architecture diagram, plan review, or complex comparison table during
CMMC advisory work:

1. Read `{skill-root}/references/grc/companion-stack.md` in the CMMC Advisor
   skill root to confirm visual-explainer is appropriate (ad hoc recap) vs
   `{skill-root}/scripts/generate_dashboard.py` or
   `{skill-root}/scripts/generate_diagrams.py` (authoritative program views).
2. Read the canonical `visual-explainer` skill at
   `.visual-explainer/plugins/visual-explainer/SKILL.md` (or
   `.cursor/skills/visual-explainer/SKILL.md` when symlinked). Follow its workflow
   and command templates under `commands/`.
3. Write generated HTML to `~/.agent/diagrams/` unless the user requests another
   path; open in a browser when shell access permits.

CMMC assessor rails (grill, mock-assess, red-team-scope): offer visual-explainer
when terminal output would exceed roughly 4 rows or 3 columns.

Do not treat visual-explainer HTML as assessment evidence without copying
conclusions into program data and regenerating the dashboard/SSP.
